cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about a method for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method that combines two competing paradigms, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper introduces a differentiable region-to-pixel layer and a differentiable free-form Region-of-Interest pooling layer, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on two datasets, which involves performance evaluation (cs.MM - Multimedia).
